Data Science Lab 6 Notes

REVISION
Structure: Vector
Dim: 1D
Data Type: Char/Num
Syntax: v <- c(1,2,100)

Structure: List
Dim: 1D
Data Type: Different
Syntax: a <- list(Name = "Ali", Age = 25, Scores = c(80, 65))

Structure: Matrix
Dim: 2D
Data Type: Numerical
Syntax: m <- matrix(7:12, nrow = 3, ncol = 2)

Structure: Array
Dim: >= 2D
Data Type: Numerical
Syntax: arr <- array(13:24, dim = c(3, 2, 2)) //Row, Column, How Many Table
_______________________
Data Frame
Its like a datasheet or database that stores multiple data.
_______________________
Selection Statement vs Looping Structure

Selection
if-else

Looping
1. for loop (we know how many we will iterate)
2. while (check condition once then do the loop)
3. repeat (it will do the loop at least one)
_______________________
Factorise
- Grouping of the data
_______________________
cat - print the string then the value/variable
print - to only display the content of the data
str - to display the structure of the data